text:
So are we surprised seeing this title or watching sehun being his true self? 
No. That provides enough proof to say how real he is to us on camera every time since his debut. Mentioning how he practically grew Infront of cameras there is no pretense in him. He is just real with us. Like friends. It is this honesty that I miss. 
Not him but Exo in general are honest in front of camera which obviously comes off rude to each other. But in reality that is how we all act with our group of friends. 
Sehun learned from the best people. Where he does exhibit his own persona most of the time but it also reflects how other exo members are coz they raised him like big brothers.
I can't wait for more content.

author: @hunniepyeon7722
text: I just find the question mark "?" title which Sehun had used for his first ever vlog so perfectly fitting. It fits him so much because he is just like a question mark himself. Others might know him as the maknae of exo, spoiler fairy or etc. but he has so much depth in him that even if you already know him, you end up questioning your self if you actually really knew him whenever he shows a new side. He is so realistic, pure and funny in his own way. I love the fact how he knows how to appreciate even the little things and he finds joy and peace with nature. Sehun is simple but he has got so much layers in him which he has yet to unveil. Been a fan of his for years since debut days but each time he never fails to amaze me, there is indeed not many idol like him. An idol who makes you not only love him when his on stage or on camera performing but an idol who makes you admire him for his beautiful personality.

author: @warriorlight417
text:
Alternatively, this can be titled "Just Sehun". Just like the drive started with "Just us 2", I'd believe Sehun wanted to show this "just Sehun" side of him "silently". Where we would just watch him closely and get to know this side of him silently, calmly - like we were going through this short trip with him when cameras aren't rolling and there is no script/no theme/nothing else but that moment. 

Sadly, it has to be with a camera ğŸ¤£

But also? 


I have been imagining Sehun, if he had a "show", just like this. He'd discover places, people, listen to their stories, happily experience even the "little things" and take all the goodness he could from that experience.

I didn't know I'd be getting it this way, so...color me super grateful for this. Like a tiny miracle on my end. 

"Just Sehun", I hope to see and hear from you more. ğŸ¤
